The question asks to evaluate the divergence of the vector field \( \mathbf{u} = x^2 \mathbf{i} + e^{xy} \mathbf{j} + xyz \mathbf{k} \) at the point \((-1, 1, 2)\).  
The divergence is \( \nabla \cdot \mathbf{u} = 2x + x e^{xy} + xy \). Substituting \((-1, 1, 2)\) gives \( 2(-1) + (-1)e^{-1} + (-1)(1) = -2 - e^{-1} - 1 = -3 - e^{-1} \).  

\boxed{D}
